headline: Elon Musk Sets Self-Driving Tesla Robotaxi Countdown To Three Weeks
summary: Tesla CEO Elon Musk doubled down Tuesday on his claim that "safety monitors" will be removed from Austin, Texas, "robotaxi" Model Y vehicles in the EV giant's ride-hailing fleet by the end of 2025.  TSLA edged higher early before reversing lower in Wednesday's stock market.  In a videoconference at a xAI "hackathon" event on Tuesday afternoon, Musk said that unsupervised full self-driving is "pretty much solved at this point" and that "there will be Tesla robotaxis operating in Austin with no one in them, not even anyone in the passenger seat, in about three weeks."

headline: Elon Musk says DOGE was only 'somewhat successful' and he wouldn't do it again
summary: Mega billionaire Elon Musk, in a friendly interview with his aide and conservative influencer Katie Miller, said his efforts leading the Department of Government Efficiency were only “somewhat successful” and he would not do it over again.  The Tesla and SpaceX CEO, who also owns the social media platform X, still broadly defended President Donald Trump's controversial pop-up agency that Musk left in the spring before it shuttered officially last month.

headline: Talk of an AI bubble is just 'ridiculous,' this strategist says
summary: Investors are still going back and forth over whether there is an AI bubble surrounding markets (^DJI, ^IXIC, ^GSPC) or whether it is going to pop soon. One Wall Street analyst finds the chatter over the existence of an AI bubble "ridiculous." Humilis Investment Strategies CEO and Chief Investment Officer Brian Belski sits down with Market Catalysts host Julie Hyman to explain his thoughts on the AI trade, dynamic changes since the Dot-Com Bubble of the 1990s, and his view on the Magnificent Seven tech stocks. headline: How Big Tech's AI build-out is 'mostly' a private credit story
summary: Big Tech companies are spending trillions to build out data centers, and the $40 trillion private credit market is supporting that build-out in a way public investors may not realize. As part of Yahoo Finance's exclusive coverage with executives at Apollo Global (APO), Yahoo Finance Executive Editor Brian Sozzi sits down with Apollo Global Management's co-head of corporate credit, John Cortese, to discuss how artificial intelligence (AI) infrastructure is a private credit story and to explain what investors get wrong about the space. headline: Tesla Stock Is Deutsche Bank’s Top Car Pick for 2026. It’s About Much More Than EVs.
summary: Investors looking for a winning car stock might just have to go with  Tesla  according to Deutsche Bank analyst Edison Yu.  On Tuesday, Deutsche released its automotive outlook for the coming year, and Tesla is one of Yu’s “top picks.”  Its car business might underperform in 2026, amid easing climate regulations in both the U.S. and Europe and “intensifying” competition in China—but the forecast is about more than that.
